For all integers $n$ greater than 1, define $a_n =
\dfrac{1}{\log_n 2002}$. Let $b = a_2 + a_3 + a_4 + a_5$ and $c=
a_{10} + a_{11} + a_{12} + a_{13} + a_{14}$. Find $b - c.$

$a_n = \frac{1}{\log_n 2002} = \frac{1}{\frac{\ln 2002}{\ln n}} = \frac{\ln n}{\ln 2002}$.

$b = a_2 + a_3 + a_4 + a_5 = \frac{\ln 2}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 3}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 4}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 5}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 2 + \ln 3 + \ln 4 + \ln 5}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln (2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4 \cdot 5)}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 120}{\ln 2002}$.

$c = a_{10} + a_{11} + a_{12} + a_{13} + a_{14} = \frac{\ln 10}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 11}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 12}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 13}{\ln 2002} + \frac{\ln 14}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 10 + \ln 11 + \ln 12 + \ln 13 + \ln 14}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln (10 \cdot 11 \cdot 12 \cdot 13 \cdot 14)}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 240240}{\ln 2002}$.

$b - c = \frac{\ln 120}{\ln 2002} - \frac{\ln 240240}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 120 - \ln 240240}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln \frac{120}{240240}}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln \frac{1}{2002}}{\ln 2002} = \frac{\ln 2002^{-1}}{\ln 2002} = \frac{-\ln 2002}{\ln 2002} = -1$.

Final Answer: $\boxed{-1}$
